     5тЖТ## Code of Conduct
     6тЖТ
     7тЖТAll interactions in the **npm** organization on GitHub are considered to be covered by our standard [Code of Conduct](https://docs.npmjs.com/policies/conduct).
     8тЖТ
     9тЖТ## Reporting Bugs
    10тЖТ
      тЖТтАж
    17тЖТ## Pull Request Conventions
    18тЖТ
    19тЖТ### Commits
    20тЖТ
    21тЖТWe use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).
    22тЖТ
    23тЖТWhen opening a pull request please be sure that either the pull request title, or each commit in the pull request, has one of the following prefixes:
    24тЖТ
    25тЖТ - `feat`: For when introducing a new feature.  The result will be a new semver minor version of the package when it is next published.
    26тЖТ - `fix`: For bug fixes. The result will be a new semver patch version of the package when it is next published.
    27тЖТ - `docs`: For documentation updates.  The result will be a new semver patch version of the package when it is next published.
    28тЖТ - `chore`: For changes that do not affect the published module.  Often these are changes to tests.  The result will be *no* change to the version of the package when it is next published (as the commit does not affect the published version).
    29тЖТ
    30тЖТ### Test Coverage
    31тЖТ
